{
  "doc_id": "51920",
  "text": "The cytoplasmic domain of Syt IV strongly inhibited the Ca 2+ -dependent stimulation of soluble N-ethylmaleimide sensitive factor-attachment receptor (SNARE)-mediated liposome fusion by Syt I 7 . In contrast, Syt IV expression had no effect on synaptic function in hippocampal cultures [CITATION_1] . Reports on the function of the Drosophila Syt IV homolog are also quite divergent [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , but the primary structures of rodent and Drosophila Syt IV differ sufficiently to raise questions about the relevance of these findings to data presented here.",
